-- Molson Coors "confident of clearance" for U.S. deal
-- 
-- Tue Oct 9, 2007 9:52am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/10/09/us-sabmiller-molsoncoors-clearance-idUSL0910355720071009

 

 LONDON  (Reuters) - Molson Coors Brewing ( TAP.N ) on Tuesday said it was confident of getting regulatory clearance for a brewing joint venture to combine its U.S. brewing operations with those of SABMiller Plc ( SAB.L ). 

 "We are confident of clearance. We believe this is a pro-competitive transaction," Molson Coors Chief Executive Leo Kiely told a briefing after the deal was announced. Kiely will become chief executive of the U.S. joint venture to be called MillerCoors.